WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:07.350
JOEL LEWIS: Hi.

00:00:07.350 --> 00:00:08.970
Welcome back to recitation.

00:00:08.970 --> 00:00:11.540
Today I wanted to talk about
something that's mentioned in

00:00:11.540 --> 00:00:13.300
the notes but wasn't
covered in lecture

00:00:13.300 --> 00:00:15.250
because of the exam review.

00:00:15.250 --> 00:00:19.780
So this is, the subject is
hyperbolic trig functions.

00:00:19.780 --> 00:00:23.320
So first I just wanted to define
them for you and graph

00:00:23.320 --> 00:00:25.110
them so we can get a little
bit of a feeling for what

00:00:25.110 --> 00:00:27.690
these functions are like, and
then I'm going to explain to

00:00:27.690 --> 00:00:30.480
you why they have the
words hyperbolic and

00:00:30.480 --> 00:00:32.440
trig in their names.

00:00:32.440 --> 00:00:36.180
So these are some interesting
functions.

00:00:36.180 --> 00:00:39.500
They're not, they don't, aren't
quite as important as

00:00:39.500 --> 00:00:43.470
your usual, sort of circular
trig functions.

00:00:43.470 --> 00:00:47.340
But yeah, so let me introduce
them and let me jump in just

00:00:47.340 --> 00:00:48.520
with their definition.

00:00:48.520 --> 00:00:51.340
So there are two most
important ones.

00:00:51.340 --> 00:00:53.150
Just like a regular
trigonometric functions

00:00:53.150 --> 00:00:55.750
there's the sine and the cosine
and then you can write

00:00:55.750 --> 00:00:58.370
the other four trigonometric
functions in terms of them.

00:00:58.370 --> 00:01:00.560
So for hyperbolic trig
functions we have the

00:01:00.560 --> 00:01:03.260
hyperbolic scoine and
the hyperbolic sine.

00:01:03.260 --> 00:01:06.760
So the notation here,
we write c o s h.

00:01:06.760 --> 00:01:08.970
So the h for hyperbolic.

00:01:08.970 --> 00:01:10.560
So hyperbolic cosine.

00:01:10.560 --> 00:01:14.960
And usually we pronounce this
"cosh." And similarly, for the

00:01:14.960 --> 00:01:19.020
hyperbolic sine we write s i n
h, for hyperbolic sine, except

00:01:19.020 --> 00:01:20.180
in the reverse order.

00:01:20.180 --> 00:01:23.610
And we usually pronounce this
"sinch," so in American

00:01:23.610 --> 00:01:25.630
English as if there were
an extra c in there.

00:01:25.630 --> 00:01:27.360
Sinch.

00:01:27.360 --> 00:01:27.580
OK.

00:01:27.580 --> 00:01:31.410
So these functions have fairly
simple definitions in terms of

00:01:31.410 --> 00:01:32.960
the exponential function--

00:01:32.960 --> 00:01:33.570
e to the x.

00:01:33.570 --> 00:01:38.765
So cosh of x is defined to be e
to the x plus e to the minus

00:01:38.765 --> 00:01:40.470
x divided by 2.

00:01:40.470 --> 00:01:45.730
And sinh of x is defined to be
e to x minus e to the minus x

00:01:45.730 --> 00:01:47.030
divided by 2.

00:01:47.030 --> 00:01:50.340
So if you remember what your
graph of e to the x looks

00:01:50.340 --> 00:01:53.100
like, and your graph of e to the
minus x, it's not hard to

00:01:53.100 --> 00:01:57.930
see that the graphs of cosh x
and sinh x, should look sort

00:01:57.930 --> 00:01:58.360
of like this.

00:01:58.360 --> 00:02:03.280
So for cosh x, so we see as x
gets big, so e to the minus x

00:02:03.280 --> 00:02:04.150
is going to 0.

00:02:04.150 --> 00:02:05.220
It's not very important.

00:02:05.220 --> 00:02:08.210
So it mostly is driven by
this e to the x part.

00:02:08.210 --> 00:02:13.570
And as x gets negative and big,
then this is going to 0

00:02:13.570 --> 00:02:16.140
and this is getting
larger and larger.

00:02:16.140 --> 00:02:18.420
So we got something that
looks like this.

00:02:18.420 --> 00:02:21.200
So it looks a little bit, in
this picture it looks a little

00:02:21.200 --> 00:02:24.090
bit like a parabola, but the
growth here is exponential at

00:02:24.090 --> 00:02:24.650
both sides.

00:02:24.650 --> 00:02:26.900
So in fact, this is growing
much, much, much faster than,

00:02:26.900 --> 00:02:29.270
say 1 plus x squared.

00:02:29.270 --> 00:02:30.730
So it's a much steeper curve.

00:02:30.730 --> 00:02:33.010
OK.

00:02:33.010 --> 00:02:36.070
And it reaches its minimum here
at x equals 0-- it has

00:02:36.070 --> 00:02:38.780
the value 1 plus 1 over 2.

00:02:38.780 --> 00:02:42.850
So its minimum there is
x equals 0 as its

00:02:42.850 --> 00:02:45.140
minimum value 1.

00:02:45.140 --> 00:02:47.080
For sinh, OK, so we're taking
the difference of them.

00:02:47.080 --> 00:02:52.950
So it's similar when x is
positive and large, e to the x

00:02:52.950 --> 00:02:57.720
is big, and e to the minus
x is pretty small, almost

00:02:57.720 --> 00:02:58.480
negligible.

00:02:58.480 --> 00:03:01.260
So we got exponential growth
off that side.

00:03:01.260 --> 00:03:06.180
When x becomes negative and
large, e to the x is going to

00:03:06.180 --> 00:03:10.020
0, e to the minus x is becoming
large, but it's,

00:03:10.020 --> 00:03:11.380
we've got a minus sign here.

00:03:11.380 --> 00:03:15.650
So as x goes to minus infinity,
this curve goes also

00:03:15.650 --> 00:03:16.700
to minus infinity.

00:03:16.700 --> 00:03:21.300
And again, the growth here is
exponential in both cases.

00:03:21.300 --> 00:03:24.490
And if you were curious, say
about what the slope there at

00:03:24.490 --> 00:03:27.110
the origin is, you could quickly
take a derivative and

00:03:27.110 --> 00:03:28.970
check that that's passing
through the origin

00:03:28.970 --> 00:03:31.400
with slope 1 there.

00:03:31.400 --> 00:03:31.640
OK.

00:03:31.640 --> 00:03:34.150
So this is a sort of basic
picture of what

00:03:34.150 --> 00:03:36.810
these curves look like.

00:03:36.810 --> 00:03:41.660
They have some nice properties,
and let me talk

00:03:41.660 --> 00:03:42.260
about them.

00:03:42.260 --> 00:03:47.670
So for example, one nice thing
you might notice about these

00:03:47.670 --> 00:03:49.347
functions is that it's easy to
compute their derivatives.

00:03:49.347 --> 00:03:50.830
Right?

00:03:50.830 --> 00:04:01.640
So if we look at d dx of cosh
x in order to compute that,

00:04:01.640 --> 00:04:04.440
well, just look at the
definition of cosh.

00:04:04.440 --> 00:04:07.450
So it's really just a sum of
two exponential functions.

00:04:07.450 --> 00:04:10.130
Exponential functions are easy
to take the derivatives.

00:04:10.130 --> 00:04:12.490
Take the derivative of e to
the x, you get e to the x.

00:04:12.490 --> 00:04:15.500
Take the derivative of e to the
minus x, well, OK, so it's

00:04:15.500 --> 00:04:17.790
a little chain rule so you
get a minus 1 in front.

00:04:17.790 --> 00:04:23.030
So the derivative of cosh x is
e to the x minus e to the

00:04:23.030 --> 00:04:25.310
minus x over 2.

00:04:25.310 --> 00:04:26.810
But we have a name for this.

00:04:26.810 --> 00:04:31.250
This is actually just sinh x.

00:04:31.250 --> 00:04:40.950
So the derivative of cosh is
sinh, and the derivative of

00:04:40.950 --> 00:04:42.370
sinh, well, OK.

00:04:42.370 --> 00:04:45.480
You look at the same thing, take
this formula, take its

00:04:45.480 --> 00:04:47.040
derivative, well, e to the x.

00:04:47.040 --> 00:04:48.780
Take its derivative,
you get e to the x.

00:04:48.780 --> 00:04:49.600
e to the minus x.

00:04:49.600 --> 00:04:52.240
Take its derivative, you get
minus e to the minus x, so

00:04:52.240 --> 00:04:54.860
those two minus signs cancel
out and become a plus.

00:04:54.860 --> 00:05:01.660
So this is e to the x plus
e to the minus x over 2,

00:05:01.660 --> 00:05:03.860
which is cosh x.

00:05:03.860 --> 00:05:06.550
So here you have some behavior
that's a little bit

00:05:06.550 --> 00:05:08.400
reminiscent of the behavior
of trig functions.

00:05:08.400 --> 00:05:08.980
Right?

00:05:08.980 --> 00:05:11.510
For trig functions, if you take
the derivative of sine

00:05:11.510 --> 00:05:12.520
you get cosine.

00:05:12.520 --> 00:05:14.980
And if you take the derivative
of cosine you almost get back

00:05:14.980 --> 00:05:16.390
sine, but you get minus sine.

00:05:16.390 --> 00:05:18.970
So here you don't have
that extra negative

00:05:18.970 --> 00:05:19.902
sign floating around.

00:05:19.902 --> 00:05:20.690
Right?

00:05:20.690 --> 00:05:23.050
So you, when you take the
derivative of cosh you get

00:05:23.050 --> 00:05:24.550
sinh on the nose.

00:05:24.550 --> 00:05:27.080
No minus sign needed.

00:05:27.080 --> 00:05:29.630
So that's interesting.

00:05:29.630 --> 00:05:35.140
But the real reason that these
have the words trig in their

00:05:35.140 --> 00:05:39.200
name is actually a little
bit deeper.

00:05:39.200 --> 00:05:42.810
So let me come over here and
draw a couple pictures.

00:05:42.810 --> 00:05:45.880
So the normal trig functions--

00:05:45.880 --> 00:05:49.450
what sometimes we call the
circular trig functions if we

00:05:49.450 --> 00:05:51.350
want to distinguish them from
the hyperbolic trig

00:05:51.350 --> 00:05:53.730
functions--

00:05:53.730 --> 00:05:55.420
they're closely, so circular
trig functions, they're

00:05:55.420 --> 00:05:57.560
closely related to
the unit circle.

00:05:57.560 --> 00:06:02.630
So the unit circle has equation
x squared plus y

00:06:02.630 --> 00:06:05.790
squared equals 1.

00:06:05.790 --> 00:06:06.820
It's a circle.

00:06:06.820 --> 00:06:09.600
Well, close enough, right?

00:06:09.600 --> 00:06:13.280
And what is the nice
relationship between this

00:06:13.280 --> 00:06:14.860
circle and the trig functions?

00:06:14.860 --> 00:06:19.370
Well, if you choose any point
on this circle, then there

00:06:19.370 --> 00:06:23.130
exists some value of t such
that this point has

00:06:23.130 --> 00:06:28.890
coordinates cosine
t comma sine t.

00:06:28.890 --> 00:06:32.550
Now it happens that the value
of t is actually the angle

00:06:32.550 --> 00:06:35.430
that that radius makes with
the positive axis.

00:06:35.430 --> 00:06:37.240
But not going to worry
about that right now.

00:06:37.240 --> 00:06:40.830
It's not the key
idea of import.

00:06:40.830 --> 00:06:46.380
So as t varies through the real
numbers, the point cosine

00:06:46.380 --> 00:06:50.130
t, sine t, that varies and it
just goes around this curve.

00:06:50.130 --> 00:06:52.530
So it traces out this
circle exactly.

00:06:52.530 --> 00:06:57.370
So the hyperbolic trig functions
show up in a very

00:06:57.370 --> 00:06:58.670
similar situation.

00:06:58.670 --> 00:07:01.600
But instead of looking at the
unit circle, what we want to

00:07:01.600 --> 00:07:04.580
look at is the unit rectangular
hyperbola.

00:07:04.580 --> 00:07:05.650
So what do I mean by that?

00:07:05.650 --> 00:07:08.720
Well, so instead of taking the
equation x squared plus y

00:07:08.720 --> 00:07:11.790
squared equals 1, which gives a
circle, I'm going to look at

00:07:11.790 --> 00:07:14.310
a very similar equation that
gives a hyperbola.

00:07:14.310 --> 00:07:18.780
So this is the equation,
x squared minus y

00:07:18.780 --> 00:07:21.690
squared equals 1.

00:07:21.690 --> 00:07:29.250
So if you if you graph this
equation, what you'll see is

00:07:29.250 --> 00:07:32.250
that, well, it passes through
the point 1, 0.

00:07:32.250 --> 00:07:39.720
And then we've got one branch
here, we've got a little out

00:07:39.720 --> 00:07:40.970
asymptote there.

00:07:45.120 --> 00:07:49.250
So it's got a right branch
like that, and also it's

00:07:49.250 --> 00:07:51.760
symmetric across the y-axis.

00:07:51.760 --> 00:08:00.570
So there's a symmetric
left branch here.

00:08:00.570 --> 00:08:04.700
So this is the graph of the
equation, x squared minus y

00:08:04.700 --> 00:08:05.890
squared equals 1.

00:08:05.890 --> 00:08:09.200
So it's this hyperbola.

00:08:09.200 --> 00:08:14.520
Now what I claim is that cosh
and sinh have the same

00:08:14.520 --> 00:08:17.690
relationship to this hyperbola
as cosine and

00:08:17.690 --> 00:08:19.020
sine have to the circle.

00:08:19.020 --> 00:08:21.180
Well, so I'm fudging
a little bit.

00:08:21.180 --> 00:08:24.440
So it turns out it's only the
right half of the hyperbola.

00:08:24.440 --> 00:08:25.610
So what do I mean by that?

00:08:25.610 --> 00:08:28.210
Well, here's what
I'd like to do.

00:08:28.210 --> 00:08:31.180
Set x equals--

00:08:31.180 --> 00:08:33.910
so we're going to introduce
a new variable, u--

00:08:33.910 --> 00:08:41.090
I'm going to set x equal cosh
u and y equals sinh u.

00:08:41.090 --> 00:08:43.760
And I'm going to look
at the quantity x

00:08:43.760 --> 00:08:44.850
squared minus y squared.

00:08:44.850 --> 00:08:48.770
So x squared minus y squared.

00:08:51.610 --> 00:08:53.630
So this is, so we use most
of the same notations for

00:08:53.630 --> 00:08:55.270
hyperbolic trig functions
that we do for

00:08:55.270 --> 00:08:56.170
regular trig functions.

00:08:56.170 --> 00:09:04.820
So this is cosh squared u
minus sinh squared u.

00:09:04.820 --> 00:09:07.246
And now we can plug in the
formulas for cosh and sinh

00:09:07.246 --> 00:09:14.290
that we have. So this is equal
to e to the u plus e to the

00:09:14.290 --> 00:09:21.430
minus u over 2 quantity squared
minus e to the u minus

00:09:21.430 --> 00:09:25.990
e to the minus u over
2 quantity squared--

00:09:25.990 --> 00:09:29.700
and now we can expand out both
of these factors and, both of

00:09:29.700 --> 00:09:33.070
these squares, rather, and
put them together.

00:09:33.070 --> 00:09:37.930
So over 2 squared is over 4 and
we square this and we get

00:09:37.930 --> 00:09:39.860
e to the 2u.

00:09:39.860 --> 00:09:43.260
OK, so then we get 2 times e to
the u times e to the minus

00:09:43.260 --> 00:09:45.710
u-- but e to the u times e to
the minus u is just 1--

00:09:45.710 --> 00:09:57.910
so plus 2 plus e to the minus
2u minus e to the 2u minus 2

00:09:57.910 --> 00:10:01.360
plus e to the minus 2u-- so
same thing over here--

00:10:01.360 --> 00:10:03.840
over 4.

00:10:03.840 --> 00:10:06.940
OK, so the e to the 2u's cancel
and the e to the minus

00:10:06.940 --> 00:10:09.580
2u's cancel and we're left
with 2 minus minus 2.

00:10:09.580 --> 00:10:10.420
That's 4.

00:10:10.420 --> 00:10:14.000
So this is 4 over 4, so
this is equal to 1.

00:10:14.000 --> 00:10:14.360
OK.

00:10:14.360 --> 00:10:19.590
So if x is equal to cosh u and
y is equal to sinh u, then x

00:10:19.590 --> 00:10:21.970
squared minus y squared
is equal to 1.

00:10:21.970 --> 00:10:26.550
So if we choose a point cosh
u, sinh u for sum u, that

00:10:26.550 --> 00:10:28.850
point lies on this hyperbola.

00:10:28.850 --> 00:10:29.482
That's what this says.

00:10:29.482 --> 00:10:35.720
That this point, OK so the
point cosh u, sinh u is

00:10:35.720 --> 00:10:38.150
somewhere on this hyperbola.

00:10:38.150 --> 00:10:41.040
And what's also true is the
sort of reverse statement.

00:10:41.040 --> 00:10:45.380
If you look at all such points,
if you let u vary and

00:10:45.380 --> 00:10:48.290
look through the real numbers
and you ask what happens to

00:10:48.290 --> 00:10:52.000
this point cosh u, sinh u, the
answers is that it traces out

00:10:52.000 --> 00:10:53.700
the right half of
this hyperbola.

00:10:53.700 --> 00:10:57.350
If you go back to the graph of
y equals cosh x, you'll see

00:10:57.350 --> 00:11:00.580
that the hyperbolic cosine
function is always positive.

00:11:00.580 --> 00:11:02.160
So we can't--

00:11:02.160 --> 00:11:04.070
over here-- we can't
trace out this left

00:11:04.070 --> 00:11:05.610
branch where x is negative.

00:11:05.610 --> 00:11:08.260
Although it's easy enough to say
what does trace out this

00:11:08.260 --> 00:11:09.950
left branch.

00:11:09.950 --> 00:11:13.760
Since it's just the mirror
image, this is traced out by

00:11:13.760 --> 00:11:18.740
minus cosh u comma sinh u.

00:11:22.220 --> 00:11:24.520
So there's a, so the hyperbolic
trig functions have

00:11:24.520 --> 00:11:28.430
the same relationship to this
branch of this hyperbola that

00:11:28.430 --> 00:11:31.120
the regular trig functions
have to the circle.

00:11:31.120 --> 00:11:34.590
So there's where the words
hyperbolic and trig

00:11:34.590 --> 00:11:36.120
functions come from.

00:11:36.120 --> 00:11:39.680
So let me say one more thing
about them, which is that we

00:11:39.680 --> 00:11:44.100
saw that they have
this analogy with

00:11:44.100 --> 00:11:45.125
regular trig functions.

00:11:45.125 --> 00:11:45.560
Right?

00:11:45.560 --> 00:11:48.310
So instead of satisfying cosine
squared plus sine

00:11:48.310 --> 00:11:52.350
squared equals 1, they satisfy
cosh squared minus sinh

00:11:52.350 --> 00:11:53.590
squared equals 1.

00:11:53.590 --> 00:11:57.130
And instead of satisfying the
derivative of sine equals

00:11:57.130 --> 00:12:00.420
cosine and the derivative of
cosine equals minus sine, they

00:12:00.420 --> 00:12:04.450
satisfy derivative of cosh
equals sinh and derivative of

00:12:04.450 --> 00:12:05.990
sinh equals cosh.

00:12:05.990 --> 00:12:07.690
So similar relationships.

00:12:07.690 --> 00:12:09.680
Not exactly the same,
but similar.

00:12:09.680 --> 00:12:13.170
So this is true of a lot of
trig relationships that

00:12:13.170 --> 00:12:16.680
there's a corresponding formula
for the hyperbolic

00:12:16.680 --> 00:12:17.560
trig functions.

00:12:17.560 --> 00:12:22.670
So one example of such a formula
is your, for example,

00:12:22.670 --> 00:12:24.790
your angle addition formulas.

00:12:24.790 --> 00:12:28.160
So I'm going to just leave this
is an exercise for you.

00:12:28.160 --> 00:12:32.390
So let me, I guess I'll just
stick it in this funny little

00:12:32.390 --> 00:12:33.640
piece of board right here.

00:12:36.480 --> 00:12:37.730
So, exercise.

00:12:41.530 --> 00:13:03.580
Find sinh of x plus y and cosh
of x plus y in terms of sinh

00:13:03.580 --> 00:13:14.380
x, cosh x, sinh y, and cosh y.

00:13:14.380 --> 00:13:18.150
So in other words, find the
corresponding formula to the

00:13:18.150 --> 00:13:20.160
angle addition formula
in that case of the

00:13:20.160 --> 00:13:21.980
hyperbolic trig functions.

00:13:21.980 --> 00:13:23.960
So I'll leave you with that.